For NamedCommands to be used in your code, you have to ensure that NamedCommands.registerCommands is run BEFORE you create any pathplanner autos. In your code, you have this.swerveSubsystem = SwerveSubsystem.getInstance(); , which runs setupPathPlanner() , which runs before this.autonomousCommands.configureAllCommands();

You will have to move this.autonomousCommands.configureAllCommand(); to be before this.swerveSubsystem, = SwerveSubsystem.getInstance().

However, something to keep in mind that the singleton pattern is not commonly used in FRC , due to it causing hard-to-diagnose issues (for example, its not abundently clear that this.swerveSubsystem = SwerveSubsystem.getInstance() is initializing it for the first time, and will run code, instead of just returning a subsystem).
